Subject: [PATCH] Relax python_requires from >=3.12 to >=3.10

Upstream uccl declares ``python_requires=">=3.12"`` in setup.py because
nanobind's stable ABI (Py_LIMITED_API / cp312-abi3 wheels) needs Python
3.12+. However, the existing code already falls back to a regular
version-specific wheel when ``sys.version_info < (3, 12)`` (see the
``_use_limited_api`` switch and the comment on the abi3 stub), so the
build itself works on Python 3.10/3.11. Relax the metadata constraint
so we can produce a cp310-cp310 wheel from this checkout.

---
diff --git a/setup.py b/setup.py
index 04b4f1ca..93e6ebfd 100644
--- a/setup.py
+++ b/setup.py
@@ -68,7 +68,7 @@ setup(
     classifiers=[
         "Programming Language :: Python :: 3",
     ],
-    python_requires=">=3.12",
+    python_requires=">=3.10",
     options={"bdist_wheel": {"py_limited_api": "cp312"}} if _use_limited_api else {},
     extras_require={
         "rocm": [],
